(44, 19, 22, 47, 8, 1, 1, 'Macedonia', 'Macedonia''s Role in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the involvement of Macedonia in the early church''s activities. Acts mentions the sending of ministers to Macedonia, while 2 Corinthians speaks of the grace of God bestowed on the churches there.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 22, 52, 1, 8, 8, 'Macedonia', 'Macedonia''s Role in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the significance of Macedonia in the spread of the Gospel. Acts 19:22 mentions sending ministers to Macedonia, while 1 Thessalonians 1:8 notes the faith spreading from Macedonia.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 23, 44, 19, 9, 9, 'that way', 'Connection of ''that way''', 'Both passages emphasize ''that way'' as a reference to the early Christian movement. The stir mentioned in Acts 19:23 arises from the opposition faced by those who followed ''that way'' in Acts 19:9.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 23, 44, 24, 22, 22, 'that way', 'Connection of ''that way''', 'Both passages emphasize ''that way'' as a significant movement within the early Christian community. The mention of ''that way'' in Acts 19:23 indicates a growing influence, which is acknowledged by Felix in Acts 24:22, showing his awareness of its importance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 23, 44, 9, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of ''this way''', 'Both passages emphasize ''this way'' as a reference to the early Christian movement. Acts 19:23 highlights the stir surrounding ''that way,'' while Acts 9:2 shows the pursuit of those following ''this way.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 23, 47, 1, 8, 10, 'no small stir about that way', 'Struggles in Asia', 'This connection highlights the theme of distress faced by believers in Asia. Both passages emphasize the challenges and turmoil associated with ''that way'' and the overwhelming pressures experienced.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 23, 44, 18, 26, 26, 'that way', 'Connection of ''the way''', 'Both passages emphasize ''the way'' as a significant theme in the early Christian movement. Acts 19:23 refers to a stir about ''that way,'' while Acts 18:26 discusses the teaching of ''the way of God more perfectly.''', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 23, 47, 6, 9, 9, NULL, 'Stir and Resilience in Faith', 'This connection highlights the contrast between external turmoil and internal strength. Both passages emphasize enduring challenges while maintaining a sense of life and purpose.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 24, 54, 6, 9, 10, 'no small gain unto the craftsmen', 'Connection of Wealth and Temptation', 'This connection highlights the dangers of wealth as seen in Demetrius''s gain from making silver shrines, paralleling the warning in 1 Timothy about the temptations that come with the desire for riches. Both passages emphasize how the pursuit of money can lead to destruction and sorrow.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 24, 44, 16, 16, 16, NULL, 'Economic Gain from Idolatry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of profit derived from idolatrous practices. In Acts 19:24, Demetrius profits from making shrines for Diana, while in Acts 16:16, the damsel''s soothsaying brings gain to her masters.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 24, 44, 16, 19, 19, NULL, 'Economic Impact of Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the economic consequences of the apostles'' ministry. In Acts 19:24, Demetrius profits from idol-making, while in Acts 16:19, the loss of profit leads to the persecution of Paul and Silas.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 24, 44, 19, 27, 28, 'no small gain unto the craftsmen', 'Economic Impact of Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the financial implications of worshiping Diana. Demetrius''s concern about their craft reflects the broader fear of losing economic stability tied to the temple''s significance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 24, 44, 19, 34, 35, 'no small gain unto the craftsmen', 'Connection between Demetrius and Diana', 'This connection highlights the economic impact of the worship of Diana in Ephesus, as Demetrius, a silversmith, profited from creating shrines for her. Both passages emphasize the significance of Diana to the local craftsmen and the community''s identity.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 24, 23, 56, 11, 12, 'brought no small gain', 'Greed and Material Gain', 'This connection highlights the theme of greed present in both passages. Demetrius, as a silversmith, represents those who seek profit, paralleling the ''greedy dogs'' in Isaiah who pursue their own gain.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 25, 28, 12, 7, 8, 'by this craft we have our wealth', 'Wealth and Deceit in Labor', 'This connection highlights the theme of wealth gained through deceitful practices. Both passages address the pursuit of riches and the moral implications of such labor, with Acts focusing on craft and Hosea on deceit in commerce.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 25, 44, 16, 19, 19, 'by this craft we have our wealth', 'Economic Impact of Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the financial consequences of the apostles'' actions. In Acts 19:25, the craftsmen express concern over their wealth, while in Acts 16:19, the masters react to a loss of gain due to Paul and Silas''s ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 25, 28, 4, 8, 8, 'by this craft we have our wealth', 'Wealth and Iniquity Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of wealth derived from iniquity. In Acts, the craftsmen acknowledge their wealth from their craft, while in Hosea, the priests consume the sin of the people, indicating a relationship between economic gain and moral corruption.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 25, 61, 2, 3, 3, 'by this craft we have our wealth', 'Connection of Wealth and Covetousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of wealth derived from craft in Acts and the warning against covetousness in 2 Peter. Both passages emphasize the dangers of prioritizing material gain and exploitation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 25, 66, 18, 3, 3, 'by this craft we have our wealth', 'Wealth and Merchants Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of wealth generated through commerce. Acts 19:25 speaks of wealth from a craft, while Revelation 18:3 highlights merchants growing rich through delicacies.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 25, 66, 18, 11, 19, 'by this craft we have our wealth', 'Wealth and Merchants', 'This connection highlights the theme of wealth derived from trade and the mourning of merchants over lost prosperity. Both passages emphasize the economic impact of a significant city, with Acts mentioning wealth from craft and Revelation depicting merchants lamenting their lost riches.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 26, 44, 17, 29, 29, 'no gods, which are made with hands', 'Connection on Idolatry and Godhead', 'This connection highlights the rejection of idols made by human hands. Both passages emphasize that God is not comparable to physical objects like gold or silver.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 26, 46, 8, 4, 4, 'no gods, which are made with hands', 'Idols and False Gods', 'This connection highlights the theme of idolatry, as both passages address the nature of idols and their lack of true divinity. Acts 19:26 emphasizes that Paul turns people away from idols, while 1 Corinthians 8:4 asserts that an idol is nothing in the world.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 26, 23, 44, 10, 20, 'no gods, which are made with hands', 'Idolatry and False Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of worshiping man-made idols. Acts 19:26 highlights Paul''s message against gods made with hands, paralleling Isaiah 44:10-20''s critique of those who create and worship graven images.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 26, 5, 4, 28, 28, 'which are made with hands', 'Connection of Idolatry and False Gods', 'This connection highlights the theme of false gods made by human hands. Both passages address the futility of worshiping idols that cannot see or hear, emphasizing the contrast between true worship and idolatry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 26, 44, 14, 15, 15, 'turned away much people, saying that they be no gods', 'Turning from Idols to God', 'Both passages emphasize turning away from false gods and vanities to worship the living God. Acts 19:26 mentions turning away from made gods, while Acts 14:15 calls for turning from vanities to the Creator.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 26, 66, 9, 20, 20, 'which are made with hands', 'Idolatry and Human Craftsmanship', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of worshipping idols made by human hands. Acts 19:26 highlights Paul''s message against such gods, while Revelation 9:20 warns against the works of their hands that lead to idolatry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 26, 24, 10, 11, 11, 'no gods, which are made with hands', 'Idolatry and False Gods', 'This connection highlights the rejection of idols, as Paul states that they are ''no gods, which are made with hands,'' paralleling Jeremiah''s assertion that gods not made by God will perish. Both passages emphasize the futility of worshipping man-made deities.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
